1. The Calligram Logic (Theory Anchor A4)

We have rejected the "page" as a linear scroll. The grid is treated as the Shield itself. Reading is an act of traversal from the nucleating heat of the forge outward to the cooling waters of the Oceanus.

The Topology

The 24x24 grid is divided not by lines, but by Radius (r) from the center [12,12].

r < 3 (The Forge): The creative engine. High density. Here, Vulcan speaks and strikes.

r 3-5 (Cosmos): The fixed firmament. Sparse, high-brightness tags (Sun, Moon).

r 5-9 (The Human World): The widest band. Divided hemispherically:

Theta 0-180° (Upper/Right): The City of Peace (Weddings, Law).

Theta 180-360° (Lower/Left): The City of War (Ambush, Ares, Hate).

r 9-11 (The Earth): Agriculture. Ploughing, Reaping, Lions attacking Bulls.

r > 11 (The Rim): The Ocean. A bounding box of text that contains the world.

